column16:
What is your Prolific ID?

Please note that this response should auto-fill with the correct ID. If you do not see your Prolific ID, please copy and paste it in below.
column17:
You are being invited to participate in a research study titled Connection to Nature and Pro- Environmental Behavior. This study is being done by Debra Lindsay & Dr. Karen Dobkins from UC San Diego. You were selected to participate in this study because you volunteered through Prolific to receive compensation of $2.18 for participating.



The purpose of this research study is to determine people’s attitudes and behaviors towards the environment to refine how we measure one’s Connection to Nature. Your participation in this research should last approximately 15 minutes. If you agree to take part in this study, you will be asked to complete an online survey. This survey will present you with a range of questions about your attitudes and behaviors towards the environment. It will also ask you some basic demographic questions.



Your participation in this study is completely voluntary and you can withdraw at any time. You will not receive compensation if you choose not to participate, withdraw before completing, or fail to show adequate attention to the survey.



If you have questions about this project or if you have a research-related problem, you may contact the researcher(s), Debra Lindsay (dlindsay@ucsd.edu). If you have any questions concerning your rights as a research subject, you may contact the UC San Diego Office of IRB Administration at irb@ucsd.edu or 858-246-4777.



By participating in this research you are indicating that you are at least 18 years old, have read this consent form, and agree to participate in this research study. Please keep this consent form for your records.



Download a copy of this notice here.

column138:
Imagine that this ladder shows how your society is set up. 

 
At the top of the ladder are the people who are the best off - they have the most money, the highest amount of schooling, and the jobs that bring the most respect. 

 

At the bottom of the ladder - they have the least money, little or no education, no jobs or jobs that no one wants or respects. 

 

Now think about yourself in relation to your PEERS. Please tell us where you think that you would be on this ladder. Select the number of the rung that best represents where you would be on this ladder.
